Noranda to Close Its Bell Mine
About 25 of the mine's 260 full-time employees will be
kept on to decommission the property. The Bell operation
includes an open-pit copper mine and a 16,000 metric ton a
day mill. It has produced more than 1.2 million short tons of
copper concentrate since it opened in 1972.
   Noranda is a mining, forest products and oil and gas
concern.